{"title":"Classified aims to bring 2× back to MTB with SRAM-beating range","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/classified-powershift-mtb-gearing","date":1680598240000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/classified-powershift-mtb-gearing\">Classified aims to bring 2× back to MTB with SRAM-beating range</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/classified-powershift-hub-review\" target=\"_blank\">Classified </a>has released its latest offering of 2023 in the form of a Powershift-enabled MTB wheelset and wireless flat-bar shifter. The Belgian brand is already making waves with its two-speed hub-based gearing system, such as appearing at recent <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/campenaerts-worldtour-classified-powershift-hub\" target=\"_blank\">WorldTour road races</a>, and it’s now attempting a move into mountain biking too with the introduction of a 12-speed 11-40 cassette, 148mm hub spacing and new Ringshifter control.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>More is more</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classified MTB ringshift powershift hub\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-9-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Classified</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Classified has dubbed its Powershift system as the ultimate ‘front-derailleur killer’ where it aims to remove the need for an extra chainring on road and gravel bikes. It is now aiming to promote the advantages of a double gear range in mountain biking, a discipline that has almost entirely embraced wide-range 1× drivetrains in recent years. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Classified says it wants to showcase the benefits of the added gear options with its new MTB set-up, the advantages of which include smaller steps between the gears and more choices for optimal cadence in comparison to a standard 1× drivetrain.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classified MTB ringshift powershift hub\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Classified</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Mountain biking has moved on from front derailleurs in the past decade, instead favouring bigger-ratio cassettes to allow for a similar range of gears, while cutting down the risk of chain drop and mechanical issues by eliminating front shifting as well as allowing improvements to frames and linkage architecture.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Given that Classified also aims to target these issues by using an internal planetary gear system as opposed to an external one, the MTB segment was a logical next step for the Belgian brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Classified says its MTB drivetrain offers a total range of 530%, ie the difference between the highest and lowest gears. By comparison, a 1× SRAM drivetrain with a 10-52 cassette offers 520%. </p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/campenaerts-worldtour-classified-powershift-hub\">Hub gears in the WorldTour: Campenaerts to race on Classified Powershift hub</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/parcours-classified-powershift-wheels\">Parcours becomes first UK brand to bring third-party Classified Powershift wheels to market</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/classified-powershift-hub-review\">Classified Powershift hub review</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Shifting focus</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classified MTB ringshift powershift hub\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-2-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Classified</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Classified’s new flat-bar Ringshifter, designed specifically for this new configuration, connects wirelessly to the 148mm MTB thru-axle. The brand says the Ringshifter can operate up to 10,000 shifts before needing to be recharged, which uses a proprietary magnetic USB charging cable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The shifter features a magnetic backspring mechanism, toggling between the two gear options rather than using a standard click or button design.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Classified says that the Ringshifter was made to fit seamlessly into most MTB cockpits, as well as to bring ‘feather light wireless’ technology.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The bigger picture</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classified MTB ringshift powershift hub\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-6-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Classified</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Mountain biking shouldn’t exclusively be the only discipline that will benefit from this latest release however. Classified says that the new 11-40 cassette can be used with the existing 12-speed Powershift hub, using the 142mm smart thru-axle and drop bar shift button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This opens it up for use in applications like <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-a-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\">gravel </a>and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/an-introduction-to-bikepacking\" target=\"_blank\">bikepacking</a> – anywhere riders are searching for more capability from their gears. As such, the new system can be purchased in three different options: hub internals only, hub internals and shell, or as a complete MTB wheelset, in the form of the M25/30s.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classified MTB ringshift powershift hub\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Classified_MTB_ringshift_powershift_hub-7-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Classified</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The M25/30s come built onto hookless carbon rims, which have an <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/road-gravel-bike-rim-width\" target=\"_blank\">internal width</a> of 30mm and a profile of 25mm, which Classified says ‘have been developed to deal with every kind of off-road terrain.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new system comes in €2,699 for the wheelset or €1,549 for the complete hub, and the hub is available in 28-hole straight-pull or 32-hole J-bend configurations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information, head to <a href=\"https://www.classified-cycling.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">Classified</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/classified-powershift-mtb-gearing\">Classified aims to bring 2× back to MTB with SRAM-beating range</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"f9bf99e552aba22e566fc7a5986d4b638f7a8a31574640d080b31c228874c6de","category":"Cycling"}